assistant:
Use the dialog statement like this:
```
dialog(title = 'New Order', size = (width, height)) { ... };
```
This creates a new dialog window with the specified title and size. You can then add any number of fields, menu items, or other objects to this dialog using their respective statements. For example:
```
entry(label).value = 'Customer:';
menu item(label).caption = 'Order Type:';
button(caption = 'Place Order').action = this.entry(label).value;
```
These statements create three new elements in the dialog: an entry field named 'Customer', a menu item named 'Order Type', and a button named 'Place Order'. The button is connected to the entry field so when you click it, Actian 4GL OpenROAD sets the value of that field to whatever you typed into it.

You can show various types of data on your graph including numeric values, strings or even boolean flags. Some examples include:
```
series.field = 'sales';
series.color = red;
series.symbol = triangle;
series.label = 'Total Sales for Q1 2023';
```
